Semitism) compiles existing knowledge on the phenomenon of Judaeophobia throughout the ages and across the world. The second volume contains more than 650 biographies from the late classical period up to the present day: It presents not only Anti-Semites and prominent victims, but also pioneers of the enlightenment. The spectrum reaches from Pope Leo the Great, Martin Luther and Richard Wagner, to David Irving, Richard Williamson and Mahmud Ahmadineschad.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAntisemitismxHistory. 0aAntisemitism. 4aAntisemitismus. 4aBiographien. 4aNachschlagewerk. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aMihok, Brigitte, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE UND GESCHICHTE 2009z9783110219500oZDB-23-DGE0 cprintz978359824072040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978359844159240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783598441592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783598441592/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGEb2009  aZDB-23-DGGb2009  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014